H0.text: Who was said to have presented the baby Jesus with Frankincense. Caspar

H1.text: Who was said to have presented the baby Jesus with Frankincense. Melchior

H2.text: Who was said to have presented the baby Jesus with Frankincense. Gaspar

H3.text: Who was said to have presented the baby Jesus with Frankincense. Baltazar

A4.text: They paid homage to him, and presented him with 'gifts of gold and of frankincense and of myrrh.' (2.11)

A5.text: Herod, disturbed, told them that he had not heard of the child, but informed them of a prophecy that the Messiah would be born in Bethlehem.
